rComments: deadlines and expectations can get lost in translation but he genuinely wants to share knowledge and is the most reasonable and understanding prof I've ever encountered. I would take a class with him again if it was not online.

The classes have no structure. The prof repeats the same life stories all along the trimester so you always hear the same things. The grading system has no substance and is more based on artistic skills, not comprehension of the subject.

I greatly enjoyed his way of making students feel empowered by discussing key issues in our spiritual awakening. His indigenous educational methodology is quite grounded and he shows his great wisdom, yet we feel at ease with him. He is very supportive and respectful. Great experience! I would recommend him by all means!
